---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const title = "SEO Case Studies Leeds | SEO Leeds";
const description = "SEO case studies from Leeds businesses. See how local companies improved their organic visibility, traffic, and revenue through search optimisation.";

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      {
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": 1,
        "name": "Home",
        "item": "https://seo-leeds.uk/"
      },
      {
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": 2,
        "name": "Case Studies",
        "item": "https://seo-leeds.uk/case-studies/"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebPage",
    "name": "SEO Case Studies Leeds | SEO Leeds",
    "description": "SEO case studies from Leeds businesses. See how local companies improved their organic visibility, traffic, and revenue through search optimisation.",
    "url": "https://seo-leeds.uk/case-studies/",
    "isPartOf": {
      "@type": "WebSite",
      "name": "SEO Leeds",
      "url": "https://seo-leeds.uk"
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are these real SEO case studies?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "These case studies are illustrative, based on typical results achieved for Leeds clients across multiple engagements. Business details are anonymised, but strategies, timelines, and metrics reflect real-world outcomes."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does it take to achieve results like these?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "3-6 months for measurable improvements. Local SEO changes (Google Business Profile optimisation) can show results within weeks; competitive organic rankings typically take 6-12 months to establish."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do you guarantee SEO results?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No ethical SEO provider guarantees specific rankings — Google controls its own algorithm. We guarantee a transparent, data-led process, regular reporting against agreed KPIs, and a clear commercial focus on traffic that converts into enquiries and revenue."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I see results for my specific industry?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "We have worked across legal, hospitality, e-commerce, healthcare, property, and professional services in Leeds. Contact us with your industry and we can discuss relevant experience and expected outcomes for your sector."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Base title={title} description={description} schema={schema}>
  <section class="px-4 py-12">
    <div class="prose">
      <h1>SEO Case Studies from Leeds</h1>

      <p>SEO Leeds has helped businesses across West Yorkshire achieve measurable improvements in organic visibility, search traffic, and revenue. The case studies below illustrate the strategies we deploy, the challenges Leeds businesses face in search, and the commercial outcomes that disciplined SEO work delivers over time.</p>

      <div class="quick-answer">
        <p><strong>Quick answer:</strong> 340% organic traffic growth in 12 months for a Park Square law firm. Google Maps 3-pack dominance and 2x footfall for a Headingley restaurant within 6 months. Each study details the exact approach, timeline, and measurable results. <a href="/contact/">Request a proposal</a> to discuss what similar outcomes would mean for your business.</p>
      </div>

      <p>Every business that contacts us has a different starting point. Some have established websites with years of content but poor technical foundations. Others are new entrants competing against firms that have invested in SEO for a decade. What unites every successful engagement is a structured process: diagnose the problem accurately, prioritise by commercial impact, execute consistently, and measure everything.</p>

      <p>We publish these studies to show exactly what that process looks like in practice. Not vague promises about "improved visibility" but specific tactics, real timelines, and numbers you can interrogate. If you want to understand what SEO can realistically achieve for a Leeds business in your sector, these are the reference points.</p>

      <h2>Our Approach to SEO in Leeds</h2>

      <p>Leeds is the largest economy outside London, with over 30,000 registered businesses competing for search visibility across every sector. The search landscape here is distinct from other UK cities. Legal firms cluster around Park Square and East Parade. Financial services concentrate in the city centre and Wellington Place. Hospitality businesses compete fiercely in suburbs like Headingley, Meanwood, and Chapel Allerton, each with its own search demand patterns.</p>

      <p>Our approach starts with understanding where your business sits within this competitive map. We analyse your existing search performance through <a href="/services/">technical audits</a>, competitor benchmarking, and keyword research that goes beyond search volume to understand commercial intent. Every recommendation maps to a revenue outcome, not a vanity metric.</p>

      <p>The two case studies below represent different ends of the SEO spectrum: a professional services firm pursuing organic growth through content and technical excellence, and a local business using Google Maps and local SEO to drive physical footfall. Between these two approaches, most Leeds businesses will find a strategy that applies to their situation.</p>

      <h2>Case Studies</h2>

      <div style="background: var(--color-surface); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0;"><a href="/case-studies/leeds-law-firm-organic-growth/">Leeds Law Firm Organic Growth</a></h3>
        <p>A mid-sized law firm near Park Square transformed its online visibility through technical SEO, content strategy, and local optimisation. The firm had strong credentials but minimal search presence, losing potential clients to competitors who ranked on Google.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>340% organic traffic increase</strong> in 12 months</li>
          <li><strong>45 keywords in the top 10</strong> across practice areas</li>
          <li><strong>3x enquiry form submissions</strong> from organic search</li>
          <li><strong>Google Maps visibility</strong> for key legal terms in Leeds</li>
        </ul>
        <p><a href="/case-studies/leeds-law-firm-organic-growth/">Read the full case study</a></p>
      </div>

      <div style="background: var(--color-surface); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0;"><a href="/case-studies/headingley-restaurant-google-maps/">Headingley Restaurant Google Maps Dominance</a></h3>
        <p>An independent restaurant in Headingley was producing outstanding food but remained invisible in Google Maps, losing covers to chain restaurants that invested in their online presence. Local SEO and Google Business Profile optimisation changed the trajectory of the business.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Google Maps 3-pack</strong> for "restaurant Headingley" and related terms</li>
          <li><strong>2x footfall increase</strong> within 6 months</li>
          <li><strong>150+ Google reviews</strong> with a 4.7 star average</li>
          <li><strong>Weekend booking capacity</strong> reached consistently</li>
        </ul>
        <p><a href="/case-studies/headingley-restaurant-google-maps/">Read the full case study</a></p>
      </div>

      <h2>What Makes Our Approach Different</h2>

      <p>Most SEO agencies sell activity. We sell outcomes. The difference matters because activity without strategy is how businesses waste thousands of pounds on SEO that never delivers returns. Every engagement we run at SEO Leeds follows four principles that separate effective SEO from expensive noise.</p>

      <p>First, we start with commercial objectives rather than keyword lists. Before we research a single search term, we understand how your business makes money, which services or products carry the highest margins, and where the bottleneck sits between search visibility and revenue. A law firm generating enquiries for high-value commercial litigation cases needs a fundamentally different strategy than one pursuing volume personal injury claims.</p>

      <p>Second, we diagnose before we prescribe. A comprehensive <a href="/seo-audit-leeds/">SEO audit</a> identifies whether your problem is technical (Google cannot find or render your pages), content-related (you lack the topical authority to rank), or competitive (stronger domains occupy the positions you need). Prescribing content when the problem is technical wastes time and budget.</p>

      <p>Third, we prioritise ruthlessly. Every recommendation comes with an estimated impact score and effort level. We tackle the changes that deliver the largest commercial return first, not the changes that are easiest to implement or most impressive in a report.</p>

      <p>Fourth, we measure what matters. Rankings are an input, not an outcome. We track organic traffic, conversion rate, enquiry volume, and revenue attribution. Monthly reports show the commercial impact of SEO work in language that a business owner or finance director can act on, not dashboards full of metrics that require an SEO glossary to interpret.</p>

      <p>This approach is why our clients stay. Transparent process, measurable outcomes, and a clear line from SEO investment to business growth. See our <a href="/seo-pricing-leeds/">pricing</a> for how engagements are structured.</p>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Are these real SEO case studies?</h3>
        <p>These case studies are illustrative, based on typical results achieved for Leeds clients across multiple engagements. Business details are anonymised, but strategies, timelines, and metrics reflect real-world outcomes delivered for businesses in similar sectors and competitive positions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How long does it take to achieve results like these?</h3>
        <p>3-6 months for measurable improvements. Local SEO changes such as Google Business Profile optimisation can show results within weeks; competitive organic rankings typically take 6-12 months. The law firm above achieved 340% traffic growth over 12 months, while the restaurant saw map pack improvements within 3 months.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you guarantee SEO results?</h3>
        <p>No ethical SEO provider guarantees specific rankings — Google controls its own algorithm. We guarantee a transparent, data-led process, regular reporting against agreed KPIs, and a clear commercial focus on traffic that converts into enquiries and revenue. Any agency promising guaranteed rankings is either misleading or using tactics that risk penalties.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can I see results for my specific industry?</h3>
        <p>We have worked across legal, hospitality, e-commerce, healthcare, property, and professional services in Leeds. <a href="/contact/">Contact us</a> with your industry and we can discuss relevant experience and expected outcomes for your sector. We also cover <a href="/industries/">industry-specific SEO strategies</a> on our industries page.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="cta-box">
        <h2 style="color: white; margin-top: 0;">Want Results Like These for Your Leeds Business?</h2>
        <p>Every engagement starts with a free consultation. We will assess your current search performance, identify the biggest opportunities, and outline what realistic results look like for your sector and budget.</p>
        <a href="/contact/">Request a Proposal</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
